libspiro
------------------------------------------
Spiro is the creation of Raph Levien. It simplifies the drawing of 
beautiful curves.

Using bézier splines an artist can easily draw curves with the same 
slope on either side of an on-curve point. Spiros, on the other hand, 
are based on clothoid splines which make it easy to maintain constant 
curvature as well as constant slope. Such curves will simply look nicer.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-61
  libgcc1-4.3.2-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.63-10
  automake1.11-1.11-10
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.9-1
  gawk-3.1.7-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.2-2
  libtool-2.2.7a-14
  make-3.81-2
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://libspiro.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/libspiro/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libspiro-20071029-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libspiro-20071029-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libspiro-20071029-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libspiro-devel-20071029-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libspiro0-20071029-X.tar.bz2

For a list of files included in the binary package, run from the 
command-line: 'cygcheck -cd [PACKAGE]'.

